swer_id": "5806", "answer_text": "A technique between logical memory and physical memory and to get faster access time."}, {"exam_answer_id": "3218", "answer_text": "only put recently used or need page in virtual memory, if needed page not in virtual memory, swap a victom page out and swap in needed page from disk"}, {"exam_answer_id": "2123", "answer_text": "a data or a resource is loaded to memory only when it is on demand. So the virtual memory can be much larger than physical memory, that is why we can run an 64GB game on a merely 8GB RAM."}, {"exam_answer_id": "2204", "answer_text": "只將執行時需要用到的 pages 載入 main memory。
可以減少每個 process 占用的 memory 大小，讓更多 process 有機會同時運行。"}, {"exam_answer_id": "1956", "answer_text": "有被實際用到的page才會在實際的記憶體中，而沒有使用到的則會在儲存設備中。這樣可以使得logical memory大於physical memory。"}, {"exam_answer_id": "2038", "answer_text": "將記憶體分為使用者邏輯位址與實體記憶體空間，在程式需要使用時才從後備空間放入主記憶體，暫時不用的資料可不被放入，大幅提升記憶體利用效率(邏輯位址數量>實體空間)"}, {"exam_answer_id": "2059", "answer_text": "demand paging是指要用到的page才載入memory。可以更有效的使用memory空間"}, {"exam_answer_id": "1562", "answer_text": "demand paging指的是CPU要求載入記憶體分頁。因為記憶體可能很大，所以等到有需要的時候再載入會比較方便。"}]}
